Hi, 
There's a new release every month. Release notes:
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/officeupdates/update-history-office-2019

You may want to install and check that you've the version listed on this release
notes page. If yes, you're patched. 
All updates (related to security, including Office 2016) and the vulnerabilities
fixed are listed on https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/

https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/vulnerability/CVE-2023-36766
